Look at the big picture for a minute..no one cares if 8000 well to do  can afford paying 70bucks amonth(thats what it would cost me in Canada) thats not the issue.<br>
<br>
YOU are naive to believe the  standard Level of quality,service,features,and dedication and content in a standard account in this genera of games will not be adversly affected by the success of this concept. Perhaps not in EQ but if this idea is successful it will forever change that for all future games.<br>
<br>
Has anyone ever compared the home edition and professional edition of Windows XP..look at the price look at what you get.. home edition is junk they should be ashamed of releasing it and its useless IN THE HOME so pay the premium and we'll give you the features you should have got in the standard version...same @#%$ here..if they can get away with giving you less for the standard rate and giving you what you should get at a premium they will. Thats big bussiness.<br>
<br>
Thats the problem it opens the door for more of this kinda @#%$.<br>
This is an insult pure and simple because indirectly you lower the perseption of your customerbase ..got a problem no gm available..well you know our turn around time on legends is less then 20minutes perhaps you'd be happier with our premium service...Game bug eat your equipment...sorry we can't do anything about that but on our Legends server we have ingame insurance perhaps our premium service would make you happier.<br>
Still iritated that the biggest MMORPG can't figure out how to include an automapper that everyones had in RPG's since the 80's..well hell for an extra 30 dollars amonth you can have that..how can you consider that a standard feature that EVERYONE should get..sorry you gotta pay for that..<br>
STarwars online wanna be a Jedi well shoot that requires more Gm interaction for your training and advancment..only premium accounts allow Jedi players..<br>
<br>
